net.big_oh.common.algorithms.winnowing
Class WinnowingFingerprinter

java.lang.Object
  net.big_oh.common.algorithms.winnowing.WinnowingFingerprinter

public class WinnowingFingerprinter
extends java.lang.Object

A Java implementation of winnowing, a document fingerprinting algorithm. Applying the winnowing algorithm to a source document results in the generation of a set of fingerprint values, that can be used to identify partial text duplications in other source documents (that have also been fingerprinted).

Following are important arguments that you can vary to change the manner in which your source documents are fingerprinted:

  • k - The size of the k-grams generated by the fingerprinting process. Text duplications shorter than size k will not be discovered. Note that in order to compare the fingerprints for two documents (to detect duplication), both documents must have been ingerprinted using the same value for k.
  • t - The guarantee threshold. Text duplications of length t or greater are guaranteed to be discoverable.

For guidance on setting k & t values, see http://theory.stanford.edu/~aiken/publications/papers/sigmod03.pdf.

Before fingerprinting documents with the winnowing algorithm it is common to pre-process those documents to remove whitespace and transform structural elements to canonical form. For example, before fingerprinting a SQL statement, one might remove comment lines (because they are "whitespace") as well as rewrite join clauses in alphabetical order. This implementation of winnowing provides the WinnowingWhitespaceFilter and WinnowingTextTransformer classes to support whitespace removal and source document transformation respectively.

WinnowingFingerprinter

public WinnowingFingerprinter(int k,
                              int t)
                       throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
A default constructor that uses MD5 as the hashing algorithm and performs no preprocessing on source documents before fingerprinting.

Parameters:
k - The size of the document k-grams that will be fingerprinted. Set k to the largest size that will not preclude the detection of "interesting" duplicates.
t - The guarantee threshold. Duplicates of length t or greater are guaranteed to be detectable using the resulting document fingerprints.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Thrown when the values for k or t are illegal. The value for k must be greater than zero. The value for t canto be less than k.

WinnowingFingerprinter

public WinnowingFingerprinter(java.util.List<WinnowingWhitespaceFilter> whitespaceFilters,
                              java.util.List<WinnowingTextTransformer> transformers,
                              int k,
                              int t,
                              java.lang.String hashingAlgorithm)
                       throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
Parameters:
whitespaceFilters - The list of filters that will be used to remove whitespace from documents before they are fingerprinted. The definition of "whitespace" will vary across domains.
transformers - The list of transformers that are used to translate source documents to a canonical form prior to fingerprinting.
k - The size of the document k-grams that will be fingerprinted. Set k to the largest size that will not preclude the detection of "interesting" duplicates.
t - The guarantee threshold. Duplicates of length t or greater are guaranteed to be detectable using the resulting document fingerprints.
hashingAlgorithm - You might use MD5 or SHA1. In any case, select a hashing algorithm that makes accidental fingerprint collisions extremely unlikely.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Thrown when the values for k or t are illegal. The value for k must be greater than zero. The value for t canto be less than k.
